rest_of_day_open: I see it continuing mostly as last week, with most of the time at my house, with possibly a brief staycation and my friends' house, which whom I have SIP'd before, to finish building a fence and gates.  I will continue to not be able to really hang out with the girl I've been seeing, except through video chat.
critical_positive: I wondered about this during the chat- what is the criteria for a successful half-hour chat with a stranger?  We were able to keep the discussion going for longer than the minimum time easily, and despite demographic differences, found a lot to talk about regarding the current state of the country and Covid situation.  She had plenty to say, so she was a good convo partner.
critical_negative: Well, the video issues did make the interaction a little less easy to stay engaged, but being of different demographics (I'm significantly older than the convo partner, live in different area) and having less in common maybe constrained the topics we could have discussed if we had more similar experiences.

rest_of_day_open: It will be stressful. I need to study for finals and make up a large number of assignments before the end of this week. My friend is being tested for corona so waiting for the outcome of that will be stressful as well. I will try to minimize my time spent worrying and focus on work.
critical_positive: We were able to find common ground very quickly and each had details and opinions to share. We also were able to introduce new trains of thought and continue our conversation well without much silence in between trains of thought. We were able to bring up new ideas to one another and share our thoughts on one another's experiences.
critical_negative: Not much. At times it was hard to find things to talk about but not often for a long period of time. It also was slightly difficult to have an even-handed conversation because we did speak over one another a couple of times. The only issue was taking turns talking when we each had something we wanted to share.
